$ Windows registry: req query

`→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/reg_exe[reg.exe] query` allows to query the → Windows/registry[registry] for specific keys, values and data.

The most useful combination of options is probably `/s` with `/f`: it recursively searches for everything that matches a given value:
code {
C:\> reg query HKLM /s /f someData
code }


The following → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/batch-files[batch files] attempt to demonstrate a few flags and usages of `reg query`.

{ insert-values.bat

 `insert-values.bat` simply inserts a handful of keys and values under `→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software]\tq84`.
 
  gh|about-Windows-Registry|/tools/reg/query/insert-values.bat||

}
{ show.bat

 `show.bat` demonstrates a few queryes below the newly inserted `HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\tq84` key.

  gh|about-Windows-Registry|/tools/reg/query/show.bat||

}
{ cleanup.bat

  Finally, `cleanup.bat` removes the `HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\tq84` key entirely.

  gh|about-Windows-Registry|/tools/reg/query/show.bat||

}
